q | a
---|---
I know the woman whose hair is red. | 나는 머리카락이 붉은색인 여자를 안다
The man whose bike was stolen called the police. | 저전거를 도난당한 남자가 경찰을 불렀다
Look at the mountain whose top is covered with snow.    | 꼭대기가 눈으로 덮여 있는 저 산을 봐.
Sumi bought a baseball cap whose color was blue.    | 수미는 색이 파란 양구 모자를 샀다.
I have a cat whose name is Babi.    | 나는 나비라는 이름의 고양이가 있다.
Whose pencil case is this?  | (의문사) 이것은 누구의 필통이니?
Do you know whose bag it is?    | (의문사) 너는 이것이 누구의 가방인지 아니?
I know the man. His last name is White  | I know the man whose last name is White.
I'm going to buy a bike. Its color is brown.    | I'm going to buy a bike whose color is brown.
I saw a dog. Its legs are short.    | I saw a dog whose lags are short.
I met an old man whose hair was White.   | 나는 머리가 하얀 노인을 만났다.
The house whose roof is red is mine.    | 지붕이 빨간 그 집은 나의 집이다.
